@page
@using mario_portfolio.Pages
@model IndexModel
@{
    Layout = null;
    ViewData["Title"] = "Mario Syti – .NET Developer";
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=DM+Mono:wght@300;400&family=Outfit:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/site.css" />
</head>
<body>
    <div class="grain"></div>
    <nav>
        <span class="nav-logo">MS</span>
        <div class="nav-links">
            <a href="#about">About</a>
            <a href="#experience">Experience</a>
            <a href="#skills">Skills</a>
            <a href="mailto:msyti@outlook.com" class="nav-cta">Hire me</a>
        </div>
    </nav>
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-inner">
            <div class="hero-text">
                <p class="hero-eyebrow">Software Developer</p>
                <h1 class="hero-name">Mario<br><em>Syti</em></h1>
                <p class="hero-tagline">Building reliable backends in C# and .NET <br>in Copenhagen, originally from Athens.</p>
                <div class="hero-badges">
                    <span class="badge">.NET / C#</span>
                    <span class="badge">ASP.NET Core</span>
                    <span class="badge">MSSQL</span>
                    <span class="badge">Azure</span>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-actions">
                    <a href="mailto:msyti@outlook.com" class="btn-primary">Get in touch</a>
                    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/msyti" target="_blank" class="btn-ghost">LinkedIn ↗</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <img src="~/images/MarioSyti.jpg" alt="Mario Syti" class="profile-photo" />
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="about section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-label">About</div>
            <div class="about-grid">
                <div class="about-text">
                    <h2>Backend developer with a<br><em>builder's mindset.</em></h2>
                    <p>With 3+ years of hands-on experience building ERPs, CRMs, and web applications, I specialize in clean, maintainable .NET backend, applying DDD, OOP, and clean architecture to real world business problems.</p>
                    <p>I moved from Athens to Copenhagen in 2022, drawn by the city's culture and pace. Outside of code, I'm deep into finance, trading, and investing and I believe the same discipline that makes a good trader makes a good engineer: <em>consistency, patience, and a long term lens.</em></p>
                </div>
                <div class="about-facts">
                    <div class="fact"><span class="fact-number">3+</span><span class="fact-label">Years of experience</span></div>
                    <div class="fact"><span class="fact-number">2</span><span class="fact-label">Countries worked in</span></div>
                    <div class="fact"><span class="fact-number">∞</span><span class="fact-label">Lines of C# written</span></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="copenhagen section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-label">2022 — A new chapter</div>
            <div class="cph-inner">
                <div class="cph-left">
                    <h2>From Athens<br>to <em>Copenhagen.</em></h2>
                    <p class="cph-lead">In 2022 I made a deliberate decision to leave the familiar behind and move to one of Europe's most forward thinking cities. Not just for a job, but to catapult both my career and my personal development forward.</p>
                    <p class="cph-body">Athens gave me my foundations: my first lines of C#, my first clients, my first real understanding of what it means to deliver software that works. But Copenhagen offered something different, a tech culture built on trust, autonomy, and craftsmanship. The kind of environment where you grow fast because the bar is simply higher.</p>
                    <p class="cph-body">Living and working in Denmark has sharpened me in ways I didn't expect. Professionally, I stepped into a larger engineering scope at Effectmakers, full end-to-end ownership, production systems, real responsibility. Personally, I built new routines, a new city, and a clearer sense of who I am and what is my identity.</p>
                    <p class="cph-body">That decision to move, to bet on myself is one I'd make again without hesitation. And later I did.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cph-right">
                    <div class="cph-stat-stack">
                        <div class="cph-stat"><span class="cph-year">Athens</span><span class="cph-stat-label">Where it started</span><p>First .NET role, first clients, foundations built.</p></div>
                        <div class="cph-arrow">↓</div>
                        <div class="cph-stat cph-stat--highlight"><span class="cph-year">Copenhagen</span><span class="cph-stat-label">Where it levelled up</span><p>Full ownership, higher standards, personal reinvention.</p></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="experience section" id="experience">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-label">Experience</div>
            <h2>Career timeline</h2>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-meta"><span class="timeline-date">Sep 2022 – Apr 2024</span><span class="timeline-location">Copenhagen, DK</span></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                        <div class="timeline-card">
                            <div class="timeline-header"><h3>Software Developer</h3><span class="company">Effectmakers</span></div>
                            <p>
                                Created, developed and optimized backend features in C#/.NET, improving performance across multiple ERP modules.
                                Engaged in discussions and status meetings, contributing with solutions towards making both incremental and drastic changes in the backend.
                                Optimized backend performance and reduced query time by up to 65% on certain modules.
                                Maintained SQL databases, created / modified stored procedures, ensured data integrity.
                                Created API projects on .NET 7 that automated company’s productivity.
                            </p>
                            <div class="timeline-tags"><span>C# / WinForms</span><span>.NET 4.8</span><span>.NET 6/7</span><span>REST APIs</span><span>Azure</span><span>Webhooks</span></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-meta"><span class="timeline-date">Nov 2021 – Jun 2022</span><span class="timeline-location">Athens, GR</span></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                        <div class="timeline-card">
                            <div class="timeline-header"><h3>Junior .NET Developer</h3><span class="company">SSPC – Software Solution P.C.</span></div>
                            <p>Built custom ERP solutions for clients using Epsilonnet Pylon. Developed MVC web apps in C# with Razor and Entity Framework, authored complex T-SQL reports visualized in Power BI, and handled direct client delivery.</p>
                            <div class="timeline-tags"><span>C# / WinForms</span><span>ASP.NET MVC</span><span>T-SQL</span><span>Power BI</span></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="skills section" id="skills">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-label">Skills</div>
            <h2>Tech stack</h2>
            <div class="skills-grid">
                <div class="skill-group">
                    <div class="skill-group-label">Languages & Frameworks</div>
                    <div class="skill-list">
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>C#</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>ASP.NET Core (MVC, Web API)</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>.NET 4.8 / 6 / 7 / 8 / 9</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Razor Pages</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Entity Framework</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="skill-group">
                    <div class="skill-group-label">Data & Cloud</div>
                    <div class="skill-list">
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>MSSQL / T-SQL</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Azure (VMs, Repos, Portal)</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Power BI</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>REST APIs & Webhooks</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>JSON / OData</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="skill-group">
                    <div class="skill-group-label">Architecture & Practices</div>
                    <div class="skill-list">
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Domain-Driven Design (DDD)</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Clean Architecture</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>OOP</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Git / GitHub / Azure Repos</div>
                        <div class="skill-item"><span class="skill-dot"></span>Agile / Scrum</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="education section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-label">Education</div>
            <h2>Background</h2>
            <div class="edu-grid">
                <div class="edu-item"><span class="edu-year">2020 – 2021</span><div><h3>Full Stack C# Developer</h3><p>PeopleCert Education</p></div></div>
                <div class="edu-item"><span class="edu-year">2011 – 2013</span><div><h3>Engineer's Degree, Automotive Technology</h3><p>IEK Athens</p></div></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="hobbies section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-label">Beyond the code</div>
            <h2>What I'm into</h2>
            <div class="hobbies-grid">
                <div class="hobby-card">
                    <div class="hobby-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="5" width="20" height="14" rx="2" /><path d="M8 9h2m4 0h2M10 9v2M10 11H8M17 12h-2" /></svg></div>
                    <h3>Gaming</h3>
                    <p>Winter ritual. Immersive worlds and strategy games, the kind that demand focus and reward patience.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="hobby-card">
                    <div class="hobby-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" /><path d="M12 2a14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 20M12 2a14.5 14.5 0 0 1 0 20M2 12h20" /><path d="M4.5 7.5c3.5 1 7 1.5 7.5 4.5s-3.5 5-5 7" /><path d="M19.5 7.5c-3.5 1-7 1.5-7.5 4.5s3.5 5 5 7" /></svg></div>
                    <h3>Football</h3>
                    <p>Summer staple. Playing and following the game, team dynamics on the pitch mirror those in engineering.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="hobby-card">
                    <div class="hobby-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20" /><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z" /></svg></div>
                    <h3>Reading</h3>
                    <p>Mostly finance and investing books, understanding markets, human behaviour, global liquidity and the long patient game.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="hobby-card hobby-card--accent">
                    <div class="hobby-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17" /><polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13" /></svg></div>
                    <h3>Finance & Trading</h3>
                    <p>Active study of markets, macro trends, and trading psychology. Discipline, systems thinking, emotion control and risk management. Principles that have leveled my mental game.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <footer>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="footer-inner">
                <div><p class="footer-name">Mario Syti</p><p class="footer-sub">Open to new opportunities in Copenhagen and remotely.</p></div>
                <div class="footer-links">
                    <a href="mailto:msyti@outlook.com">msyti@outlook.com</a>
                    <a href="tel:+4531887322">+45 31 88 73 22</a>
                    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/msyti" target="_blank">LinkedIn ↗</a>
                    <a href="https://linktr.ee/msyti" target="_blank">Linktree ↗</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="footer-bottom"><span>© @DateTime.Now.Year Mario Syti</span></div>
        </div>
    </footer>
    <script src="~/js/site.js"></script>
</body>
</html>